## ğŸ¯ TL;DR - Quick Reference

### DAY 0 ENFORCEMENT (No Exceptions)
```
âœ… PRIMARY KEY on every table
âœ… INDEX on every foreign key
âœ… Composite indexes for top queries
âœ… pg_stat_statements enabled, no seq scans >50k rows
âœ… Access tokens â‰¤15min, refresh â‰¤7d with rotation
âœ… RLS enabled on all user-data tables
âœ… Rate limits: login 5/min, writes 30/min per user
âœ… Smoke test: signupâ†’loginâ†’createâ†’cross-tenant-block (<30s)
âœ… Autoscaling (min=1, max=3), preview TTL 48h
âœ… Logs retained 14 days max
âœ… Connection pool: 20-30 max
```

### MVP PHASE WARNINGS (Weeks 1-2)
```
âš ï¸ Missing FK indexes (warn only)
âš ï¸ Secret scanning (warn only)
âš ï¸ Query plan regressions (warn only)
âš ï¸ Bundle size increases (warn only)
âš ï¸ Dependency vulnerabilities (warn only)
```

### POST-MVP BLOCKS (Week 3+)
```
âŒ Missing FK indexes (hard fail)
âŒ RLS disabled on user data (hard fail)
âŒ Broken smoke tests (hard fail)
âŒ Detected secrets in code (hard fail)
âŒ Query plan regressions (hard fail)
âŒ High-severity vulnerabilities (hard fail)
